headline: AutoZone price target raised to $3,850 from $3,700 at BMO Capital
summary: BMO Capital raised the firm’s price target on AutoZone (AZO) to $3,850 from $3,700 and keeps an Outperform rating on the shares. The company’s Q2 results, outside of SSS, were slightly below expectations, impacted by weather headwinds and ongoing growth investments, but the management continues to sound confident that its initiatives to capture market share in what is still a very fragmented industry will gain momentum in the second half of the year, the analyst tells investors in a research not
